<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 08 at 5:34PM CDT  by NWS Houston - Galveston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Brazoria County through 600 PM CDT...
At 534 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Alvin, moving southwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Alvin, Danbury, Liverpool, Bonney and Chocolate Bayou.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
